Yes. It's better to get it over with.

72
00:05:00,160 --> 00:05:02,350
I'm not the only one who's tired of him, right?

73
00:05:02,350 --> 00:05:04,920
No, definitely not.

74
00:05:07,400 --> 00:05:10,300
- Hello.
- Hello.

75
00:05:10,300 --> 00:05:12,460
Are you going home? Give us a ride, too.

76
00:05:12,500 --> 00:05:15,750
No, we aren't going home.
We need to stop by somewhere.

77
00:05:15,750 --> 00:05:17,180
Where?

78
00:05:18,240 --> 00:05:20,640
Looks like you're going somewhere really nice.

79
00:05:20,700 --> 00:05:22,980
- Let's follow them.
- No, why...

80
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:25,900
Get in. Let's go. Just get in.

81
00:05:25,920 --> 00:05:28,110
Should we scooch a bit?

82
00:05:28,110 --> 00:05:29,340
Yes, yes.

83
00:05:29,340 --> 00:05:31,460
A little more. A little more. Right.

84
00:05:31,460 --> 00:05:33,530
- Keep going. Nice.
- My goodness. What in the world.

85
00:05:33,530 --> 00:05:36,020
Oh, yeah. Go, go, go.

86
00:05:54,590 --> 00:05:57,300
This isn't reality.

87
00:05:57,300 --> 00:06:00,200
Hey, give her time. This house takes

88
00:06:00,260 --> 00:06:02,660
some time to get used to it.

89
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:08,800
It... It feels so exotic.

90
00:06:08,800 --> 00:06:12,720
Exotic? You mean, the scenery
is exotic or something?

91
00:06:12,720 --> 00:06:14,100
Yes.

92
00:06:14,100 --> 00:06:17,110
Right here. This part.

93
00:06:17,110 --> 00:06:19,100
Over here.

94
00:06:19,100 --> 00:06:21,980
It's Serengeti!

95
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:25,930
If you put a few lions here like in a jungle,

96
00:06:25,930 --> 00:06:27,860
- it'd be exactly like Serengeti.
- There are no lions.

97
00:06:27,900 --> 00:06:31,700
There are a lot of boars in the mountains.

98
00:06:31,700 --> 00:06:34,800
There are wild dogs, too.
That's why it's Serengeti.

99
00:06:34,840 --> 00:06:35,990
Yes.

100
00:06:35,990 --> 00:06:37,240
- Good.
- Bo Hyeon,

101
00:06:37,240 --> 00:06:40,090
if boars and wild dogs fought, who'd win?

102
00:06:40,090 --> 00:06:43,250
- That's not important right now.
- No. What's important now?

103
00:06:43,250 --> 00:06:45,950
Checking this place out is. Come here.

104
00:06:45,950 --> 00:06:47,630
Wow, daebak. Look here.

105
00:06:47,630 --> 00:06:49,240
Come over here.

106
00:06:49,240 --> 00:06:51,390
Why is he here?

107
00:07:01,170 --> 00:07:04,800
I came since the borough office
is doing due diligence for repurposing.

108
00:07:04,800 --> 00:07:07,900
Did you bring Hyo Ri to show her the house?

109
00:07:07,900 --> 00:07:12,800
Thanks to someone, I'm having an open
house for the whole neighborhood.

110
00:07:12,810 --> 00:07:15,000
Hey, keep it short. Keep it short.

111
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:17,150
Wow, daebak.

112
00:07:17,200 --> 00:07:19,800
- Why are they here?
- Hyung!

113
00:07:19,810 --> 00:07:21,450
This is...

114
00:07:21,450 --> 00:07:23,830
totally daebak. I mean...

115
00:07:23,900 --> 00:07:28,000
the inside and outside are completely...

116
00:07:28,930 --> 00:07:30,700
bizarre.

117
00:07:30,700 --> 00:07:35,100
I think this is a very attractive house.

118
00:07:35,100 --> 00:07:37,190
Really, it's daebak.

119
00:07:37,200 --> 00:07:40,600
<i>He's the only one on my side,
but I don't feel comforted at all.</i>

120
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:44,200
I think I saw this house in a drama.

121
00:07:44,200 --> 00:07:47,070
A drama? What drama?

122
00:07:47,070 --> 00:07:48,160
Kingdom.

123
00:07:48,160 --> 00:07:50,050
I know that one.

124
00:07:50,050 --> 00:07:52,940
Zombies walk on roofs and stuff.

125
00:07:53,900 --> 00:07:56,710
Must be nice. You're so knowledgeable.

126
00:07:58,860 --> 00:08:01,390
The borough office people are here.

127
00:08:04,960 --> 00:08:07,100
- Hello.
- Hi.

128
00:08:24,650 --> 00:08:26,310
That house is really no good.

129
00:08:26,310 --> 00:08:28,260
No way.

130
00:08:28,260 --> 00:08:30,440
You saw the borough office
employees earlier, right?

131
00:08:30,440 --> 00:08:32,410
We already got the paperwork done.

132
00:08:32,410 --> 00:08:34,720
The house has been abandoned,

133
00:08:34,720 --> 00:08:37,330
but it'd be nice if we fixed it up well.

134
00:08:37,330 --> 00:08:39,580
It's so hard to find a house

135
00:08:39,580 --> 00:08:42,130
with a view like that these days.

136
00:08:42,130 --> 00:08:44,740
That house is what people call...

137
00:08:45,750 --> 00:08:48,020
the mountain and water location.

138
00:08:48,020 --> 00:08:50,800
Is there a river in front of the house?

139
00:08:50,800 --> 00:08:54,300
- Mountain and water?
- Mountain after mountain, more like.

140
00:08:59,600 --> 00:09:01,310
To fix the house,

141
00:09:01,310 --> 00:09:03,600
it'd cost a lot of money. Do you have money?

142
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:06,200
I have to go to the hospital now.
We'd have a lot of expenses.

143
00:09:06,230 --> 00:09:08,480
And will you stop working now?

144
00:09:08,480 --> 00:09:11,020
Whether you get back to work or get
a new job, you have to return to Seoul.

145
00:09:11,020 --> 00:09:14,330
Why would you build a house here?

146
00:09:14,330 --> 00:09:16,170
I have severance pay and a security deposit.

147
00:09:16,170 --> 00:09:18,720
And with that money, we'll upgrade the annex

148
00:09:18,720 --> 00:09:22,790
with Auntie Seon Yeong and open a restaurant.

149
00:09:22,790 --> 00:09:24,440
Restaurant?

150
00:09:24,440 --> 00:09:26,450
Can you cook or have a good personality?

151
00:09:26,500 --> 00:09:29,000
- Restaurant?
- You diss me to my face?

152
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:31,350
Just give up. We already got the paperwork done.

153
00:09:31,350 --> 00:09:33,480
I'll call them and cancel it tomorrow.

154
00:09:33,500 --> 00:09:37,100
- It's all over.
- I said you can't-

155
00:09:39,530 --> 00:09:41,200
Huh? Bo Hyeon.

156
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:44,690
Don't worry. We're joking around.

157
00:09:44,690 --> 00:09:46,210
You know, on National Geographic,

158
00:09:46,210 --> 00:09:49,180
the mom and baby growl and play around.

159
00:09:49,180 --> 00:09:51,530
That's what we're doing now, right?

160
00:09:51,530 --> 00:09:52,980
No.

161
00:09:54,100 --> 00:09:57,000
Can I get your 'best help' tomorrow?

162
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:59,500
- Sure.
- Let's leave at seven, then.

163
00:09:59,550 --> 00:10:01,070
Okay.

164
00:10:02,380 --> 00:10:04,340
- See you.
- Okay.

165
00:10:16,470 --> 00:10:18,220
Gosh.

166
00:10:18,220 --> 00:10:20,020
What's the 'best help'?

167
00:10:23,680 --> 00:10:25,060
Here comes the next box.

168
00:10:25,060 --> 00:10:26,450
It has a red label on it.

169
00:10:26,450 --> 00:10:28,600
Mixed colored roses. There's another box, right?

170
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:31,100
- Yes, another one.
- Okay.

171
00:10:33,790 --> 00:10:36,800
Red roses are here...

172
00:10:53,380 --> 00:10:54,940
You're a good worker.

173
00:10:54,940 --> 00:10:57,240
I can tell she went to medical school.

174
00:10:57,240 --> 00:10:59,070
She's good at everything.

175
00:11:00,400 --> 00:11:02,660
Will these really become flowers?

176
00:11:03,670 --> 00:11:05,490
This is called propagation.

177
00:11:05,500 --> 00:11:09,280
If you cultivate a branch from the mother plant,

178
00:11:09,280 --> 00:11:10,780
it becomes a seedling.

179
00:11:10,780 --> 00:11:13,090
If you plant the seedling in a pot,

180
00:11:13,090 --> 00:11:14,780
it grows flowers.

181
00:11:14,780 --> 00:11:16,050
How fascinating.

182
00:11:16,100 --> 00:11:20,000
Flowers and people need to grow up
away from their mother.

183
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:22,370
If the mother coddles too much,

184
00:11:22,370 --> 00:11:24,940
you can't develop on your own.

185
00:11:24,940 --> 00:11:26,150
Look at me.

186
00:11:26,150 --> 00:11:28,020
Because my mom raised me free-range,

187
00:11:28,020 --> 00:11:30,000
I turned out so well.

188
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:31,150
You're right.

189
00:11:31,150 --> 00:11:33,870
You were basically a calf.

190
00:11:33,870 --> 00:11:35,700
She made you leave at sunrise

191
00:11:35,700 --> 00:11:38,030
and not let you come home before sunset.

192
00:11:38,030 --> 00:11:41,800
How could you call a person a calf?

193
00:11:41,800 --> 00:11:44,310
- What?
- How about a bull?

194
00:11:44,310 --> 00:11:45,910
Have a cow, man.

195
00:11:47,320 --> 00:11:49,480
Bo Hyeon, bring more cases from the storage.

196
00:11:49,480 --> 00:11:51,020
Okay.

197
00:11:57,500 --> 00:12:01,030
I think she was raised like
a plant in a greenhouse.

198
00:12:01,030 --> 00:12:03,730
When a plant in a greenhouse becomes a human,

199
00:12:03,730 --> 00:12:06,280
it becomes a bookworm.

200
00:12:08,140 --> 00:12:09,530
A foxtail?

201
00:12:10,320 --> 00:12:11,470
What?

202
00:12:11,470 --> 00:12:14,190
I wasn't a plant in a greenhouse, but a foxtail.

203
00:12:14,190 --> 00:12:17,250
You have to let wild plants grow naturally,

204
00:12:17,250 --> 00:12:19,150
but my mom wanted to raise me well.

205
00:12:19,150 --> 00:12:21,440
But she couldn't afford to put me in a greenhouse.

206
00:12:21,440 --> 00:12:24,100
So, she kept watering the weed on the path.

207
00:12:24,100 --> 00:12:28,050
Not knowing I drowned and ran out of oxygen.

208
00:12:28,050 --> 00:12:30,600
I was like a sick foxtail that barely

209
00:12:30,600 --> 00:12:33,380
managed to survive.

210
00:12:33,380 --> 00:12:36,370
I was more like that than a plant in a greenhouse.

211
00:12:36,370 --> 00:12:38,490
She's different because she went to medical school.

212
00:12:38,490 --> 00:12:40,800
Look how eloquent she is.

213
00:12:48,390 --> 00:12:50,580
I like Bo Hyeon.

214
00:12:51,510 --> 00:12:52,750
How about you?

215
00:12:53,790 --> 00:12:55,900
How about you, Ms. Foxtail?

216
00:12:55,900 --> 00:12:58,200
I have high standards.

217
00:12:58,200 --> 00:13:01,220
Hey. Bo Hyeon is a good guy, okay?

218
00:13:01,220 --> 00:13:03,990
I know. So, I'm considering liking him.

219
00:13:03,990 --> 00:13:07,300
Wow, Bo Hyeon. Lucky you.

220
00:13:07,300 --> 00:13:11,690
Stop being silly and finish the rest.

221
00:13:11,690 --> 00:13:13,790
I'll stop by the post office on the way home.

222
00:13:13,790 --> 00:13:15,610
That's okay, right?

223
00:13:23,340 --> 00:13:25,580
I think we can get up to four rooms.

224
00:13:25,580 --> 00:13:28,600
I think the size would be awkward.

225
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:33,080
It won't be impossible to extend the rafters.

226
00:13:33,080 --> 00:13:35,370
- Okay.
- Oh, really?

227
00:13:35,400 --> 00:13:38,700
If this becomes spacious, it'd feel more open.

228
00:13:38,700 --> 00:13:41,300
The beams are stronger than expected.
I think it'd be okay.

229
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:42,790
Gosh, seriously.

230
00:13:42,800 --> 00:13:44,700
You're so smart.

231
00:13:44,710 --> 00:13:46,220
Pardon?

232
00:13:47,130 --> 00:13:47,980
Huh?

233
00:13:47,980 --> 00:13:49,970
- Stop.
- Well, no.

234
00:13:49,970 --> 00:13:51,730
You're so intelligent and...

235
00:13:51,730 --> 00:13:53,330
How should I say? Attentive.

236
00:13:53,330 --> 00:13:55,180
You're like that.

237
00:13:56,370 --> 00:13:58,910
You said you know a demolition team, right?

238
00:13:58,910 --> 00:14:00,050
Pardon?

239
00:14:00,050 --> 00:14:01,600
I got a call.

240
00:14:01,600 --> 00:14:03,300
Yes, sir.

241
00:14:03,310 --> 00:14:04,930
He got a call.

242
00:14:04,930 --> 00:14:07,160
Don't worry about the construction team.

243
00:14:07,160 --> 00:14:10,070
I'll assist you closely by your side.

244
00:14:10,070 --> 00:14:11,810
By my side? Assist? Why?

245
00:14:11,810 --> 00:14:14,380
Oh, he doesn't know.

246
00:14:14,400 --> 00:14:19,500
I'm pretty experienced in this field.
Pretty experienced.

247
00:14:19,500 --> 00:14:22,520
- Okay, stop.
- Yes, I'll help you.

248
00:14:22,520 --> 00:14:25,370
I'll do my best. Don't worry.

249
00:14:25,370 --> 00:14:28,240
I'll stay right by your side.

250
00:14:28,240 --> 00:14:30,050
I should go to Seoul to check out materials.

251
00:14:30,050 --> 00:14:32,030
Really? Let me come with you.

252
00:14:32,030 --> 00:14:34,000
Check out the materials,
meet the construction team

253
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:35,890
- and see our place, too.
- Okay, okay.

254
00:14:35,900 --> 00:14:40,000
Should we go get makgeolli
since we're in a good mood?

255
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:41,680
- What makgeolli?
- How does that sound?

256
00:14:41,680 --> 00:14:43,170
Let's go. You and I.

257
00:14:43,170 --> 00:14:44,500
- Where? Where? Just us two?
- Get makgeolli.

258
00:14:44,500 --> 00:14:47,000
- They would feel left out, then.
- It's okay.

259
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:49,110
Don't feel left out. Come!

260
00:14:49,110 --> 00:14:51,650
- I'm sorry.
- W-What's wrong with her?

261
00:14:53,100 --> 00:14:55,050
Thank you.

262
