There are so many hidden hot spots here, right?

265
00:15:32,140 --> 00:15:33,740
Yeah.

266
00:15:34,990 --> 00:15:36,830
It's so pretty.

267
00:15:45,520 --> 00:15:47,220
Follow me.

268
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:34,290
Sorry. What do I do?

269
00:16:34,290 --> 00:16:35,980
I'm sorry.

270
00:16:37,800 --> 00:16:39,900
- I'm sorry, too.
- No, I set my foot wrong.

271
00:16:39,960 --> 00:16:41,950
I apologized in advance, okay?

272
00:16:57,700 --> 00:16:59,780
Are you crazy?

273
00:16:59,780 --> 00:17:01,430
No.

274
00:17:03,200 --> 00:17:04,790
You're wet now.

275
00:17:04,800 --> 00:17:08,400
You can cross daringly without being afraid now.

276
00:17:08,400 --> 00:17:12,810
The worst that could happen is
your feet getting a bit wetter.

277
00:17:13,980 --> 00:17:15,900
Don't be scared.

278
00:17:22,480 --> 00:17:23,920
You're right.

279
00:17:24,770 --> 00:17:26,490
I was scared for no reason.

280
00:17:28,770 --> 00:17:30,740
It feels nice and cool.

281
00:17:33,960 --> 00:17:35,350
Hey, you...

282
00:17:42,340 --> 00:17:43,900
Stop!

283
00:17:48,110 --> 00:17:50,620
Are you okay? Are you okay?

284
00:17:50,620 --> 00:17:52,240
Am I okay?

285
00:17:54,240 --> 00:17:56,570
Hold on. Hold on. Time out.

286
00:18:27,800 --> 00:18:30,190
What are you thinking about?

287
00:18:30,190 --> 00:18:32,220
What? I'm not thinking.

288
00:18:33,020 --> 00:18:35,530
Let's leave at 10 tomorrow.

289
00:18:35,530 --> 00:18:36,760
Okay.

290
00:18:36,760 --> 00:18:37,970
Are you going somewhere?

291
00:18:37,970 --> 00:18:40,920
I need to sort things out at home tomorrow

292
00:18:40,920 --> 00:18:43,740
and your mom is meeting
with the construction team.

293
00:18:43,740 --> 00:18:45,640
Will you really build that house?

294
00:18:45,640 --> 00:18:47,590
Yes, I'll take care of it.

295
00:18:47,590 --> 00:18:49,690
Don't try to argue.

296
00:19:01,430 --> 00:19:02,900
<i>Are you dead?</i>

297
00:19:02,900 --> 00:19:05,030
<i>Come quickly.</i>

298
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:09,670
Auntie, I'll go to Seoul tomorrow, too.

299
00:19:09,700 --> 00:19:11,260
Did something come up?

300
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:14,300
Are you in pain, by chance?

301
00:19:14,300 --> 00:19:15,570
I'm not.

302
00:19:15,570 --> 00:19:17,070
I'm totally fine.

303
00:19:17,070 --> 00:19:19,570
Hey, dry your hair first.

304
00:19:26,900 --> 00:19:29,510
- We'll go.
- Okay, bye.

305
00:19:36,700 --> 00:19:38,800
- Shall we?
- Yes.

306
00:19:47,090 --> 00:19:48,840
We have a tight schedule today.

307
00:19:48,840 --> 00:19:51,900
Take a nap. I'll wake you up when we arrive.

308
00:19:51,900 --> 00:19:54,200
How could I sleep now?

309
00:19:54,200 --> 00:19:56,190
Let's discuss the plan on the way

310
00:19:56,190 --> 00:19:59,080
and we should check our schedule again.

311
00:19:59,080 --> 00:20:01,990
We're in an emergency based
on the current schedule.

312
00:20:01,990 --> 00:20:05,460
And I'm too sensitive to sleep
when someone's driving.

313
00:20:24,450 --> 00:20:26,630
Emergency, she said?

314
00:20:26,630 --> 00:20:30,120
What? Sensitive, she said?

315
00:20:43,780 --> 00:20:45,490
You should have some, too.

316
00:20:48,840 --> 00:20:53,260
I'm so relieved that you guys made up.

317
00:20:53,300 --> 00:20:55,970
Because you're just like me,

318
00:20:55,970 --> 00:20:58,700
you don't hold grudges, right?

319
00:20:59,540 --> 00:21:02,320
I went to medical school because I resemble you.

320
00:21:02,320 --> 00:21:05,230
- I couldn't go near it if I took after Mom.
- Right on!

321
00:21:05,230 --> 00:21:06,710
You're exactly like me.

322
00:21:06,710 --> 00:21:08,220
Of course.

323
00:21:08,300 --> 00:21:11,990
You're perceptive and smart like me.

324
00:21:19,360 --> 00:21:21,780
- By the way...
- Yes?

325
00:21:23,830 --> 00:21:26,000
I'm not sure...

326
00:21:26,000 --> 00:21:29,410
what I should tell Sook about my illness.

327
00:21:33,200 --> 00:21:34,670
Why would you worry?

328
00:21:34,670 --> 00:21:36,510
It's Sook.

329
00:21:36,510 --> 00:21:39,610
She understands how you feel better than you.

330
00:21:41,500 --> 00:21:42,870
You're right.

331
00:21:43,690 --> 00:21:45,460
It's Sook.

332
00:21:47,140 --> 00:21:49,310
Why did I worry?

333
00:21:54,300 --> 00:21:57,600
Even if you don't explain everything,

334
00:21:57,610 --> 00:22:00,660
she'll feel it in her heart.

335
00:22:03,900 --> 00:22:05,850
We're like that, too.

336
00:22:06,990 --> 00:22:08,750
I...

337
00:22:10,100 --> 00:22:12,480
don't always have to explain.

338
00:22:26,650 --> 00:22:27,950
Hey!

339
00:22:27,950 --> 00:22:29,860
Let's go. Let's go.

340
00:22:30,860 --> 00:22:32,730
Just take it.

341
00:22:34,970 --> 00:22:38,190
Lee Hyo Ri!

342
00:22:40,030 --> 00:22:41,840
I'm here.

343
00:22:42,750 --> 00:22:46,090
- Be quiet.
- What took you so long?

344
00:22:46,090 --> 00:22:47,580
What?

345
00:22:47,580 --> 00:22:49,860
Hyo Ri!

346
00:22:57,400 --> 00:23:00,800
Are you sure you made an
appointment? It's been an hour.

347
00:23:00,840 --> 00:23:02,910
Fieldwork doesn't end on time.

348
00:23:02,910 --> 00:23:04,850
Things always change.

349
00:23:04,850 --> 00:23:06,900
You should know better.

350
00:23:06,900 --> 00:23:09,050
Are you bored?

351
00:23:09,050 --> 00:23:11,260
Should we play word chain?
Loser gets flicked on the head.

352
00:23:11,260 --> 00:23:12,710
I'm fine. I don't want to-

353
00:23:12,710 --> 00:23:14,500
Woryoil*. Five...
(Means "Monday")

354
00:23:14,500 --> 00:23:16,600
- I said I don't want to.
- Four. Three. Two...

355
00:23:16,600 --> 00:23:18,650
- Yilgwangyok*. (Means "sunbathing")
- Yok?

356
00:23:18,650 --> 00:23:19,740
Yokjeong*.
(Means "lust")

357
00:23:19,740 --> 00:23:21,270
- Hey. Come on...
- Five. Four...

358
00:23:21,270 --> 00:23:22,370
- Three.
- Jeong, jeong...

359
00:23:22,400 --> 00:23:25,000
- Two.
- Jeongyok*. Jeongyok! (Also means "lust")

360
00:23:25,910 --> 00:23:27,180
Hey, are you crazy?

361
00:23:27,180 --> 00:23:28,770
Why did you hit me? I said the word.

362
00:23:28,770 --> 00:23:30,090
You ran out of time.

363
00:23:30,100 --> 00:23:33,300
The simpler the game, the more
suspenseful it needs to be to be fun.

364
00:23:33,300 --> 00:23:36,500
And your word choice is too explicit.

365
00:23:36,500 --> 00:23:38,620
Hey. You started it...

366
00:23:39,860 --> 00:23:41,150
Let's start over.

367
00:23:41,150 --> 00:23:43,350
I'll start.

368
00:23:43,400 --> 00:23:45,940
- Sangiseuk*. (Means "foothill")
- Manager Lee!

369
00:23:45,940 --> 00:23:47,480
Chief. Let's go.

370
00:23:47,480 --> 00:23:50,000
Go where? We need to play another round.

371
00:23:50,000 --> 00:23:53,090
Oppa, we're turning 50 soon.

372
00:23:53,090 --> 00:23:55,300
Geez. Hurry up and come.

373
00:23:57,150 --> 00:23:58,790
Shit.

374
00:24:03,400 --> 00:24:06,380
I almost peed my pants
when I saw your mom that day.

375
00:24:06,400 --> 00:24:09,840
I was scared. How are you still fine?

376
00:24:11,070 --> 00:24:12,560
Congratulations on coming back.

377
00:24:12,560 --> 00:24:14,200
- Congrats.
- My friend.

378
00:24:14,200 --> 00:24:16,300
- Cheers.
- Yeah.

379
00:24:19,520 --> 00:24:22,920
The sunset, the weather, and the beer.

380
00:24:23,000 --> 00:24:26,250
I've been waiting for this day.

381
00:24:27,190 --> 00:24:29,370
I'll finish the beer and talk.

382
00:24:37,790 --> 00:24:39,560
The worksite isn't large,

383
00:24:39,560 --> 00:24:42,260
but it won't be easy since it's an old building.

384
00:24:42,260 --> 00:24:44,120
That doesn't matter.

385
00:24:44,120 --> 00:24:45,970
It's Manager Lee's house.

386
00:24:45,970 --> 00:24:49,630
I'll plaster the house even if
it were on top of the mountain.

387
00:24:49,630 --> 00:24:51,030
You're all talk.

388
00:24:51,030 --> 00:24:52,980
Another bottle of soju, please.

389
00:24:52,980 --> 00:24:54,720
- Okay.
- Mr. Jeong should be coming, too.

390
00:24:54,720 --> 00:24:56,930
Mr. Jeong?

391
00:24:56,930 --> 00:24:59,590
He must be busy with the retail complex in Songdo.

392
00:24:59,590 --> 00:25:02,360
I bragged to him that I'm building your house.

393
00:25:02,360 --> 00:25:05,310
And he got angry, saying, "Why didn't she tell me?"

394
00:25:05,310 --> 00:25:08,420
It's because I know how busy he is.

395
00:25:08,500 --> 00:25:11,720
You realize it when the titles come off.

396
00:25:11,720 --> 00:25:13,720
How you've lived your life.

397
00:25:14,700 --> 00:25:16,950
Manager Lee, you led a good life.

398
00:25:16,950 --> 00:25:19,240
Many people are helping you.

399
00:25:19,240 --> 00:25:21,460
You heard him, right?

400
00:25:21,460 --> 00:25:22,900
Here.

401
00:25:24,800 --> 00:25:27,900
Manager Lee, don't disappoint us like this.

402
00:25:27,900 --> 00:25:29,320
Hey!

403
00:25:29,320 --> 00:25:30,740
- Seriously.
- Hello.

404
00:25:30,740 --> 00:25:33,640
You bastards. They came as soon as they heard.

405
00:25:33,640 --> 00:25:36,450
This is what's wrong with you. You're too selfless.

406
00:25:36,450 --> 00:25:38,350
That's why I came so quickly.

407
00:25:38,350 --> 00:25:40,440
Sit down quickly, then. Sit.

408
00:25:40,440 --> 00:25:42,380
Bring us more soju.

409
00:25:42,380 --> 00:25:44,860
- Okay.
- Manager Lee!

410
00:25:53,750 --> 00:25:56,390
Come in! Come in! Sit.

411
00:25:56,390 --> 00:25:59,260
A box of soju, please.

412
00:26:01,480 --> 00:26:03,250
Hey, hey.

413
00:26:06,590 --> 00:26:08,810
Manager Lee,

414
00:26:08,810 --> 00:26:11,530
we bet on something.

415
00:26:11,600 --> 00:26:14,400
- You need to tell us the truth.
- Okay.

416
00:26:14,400 --> 00:26:16,500
- We go further back, right?
- What do you mean?

417
00:26:16,500 --> 00:26:20,060
- We've known each other for 14 years.
- 14 years...

418
00:26:20,060 --> 00:26:23,700
Right. Mr. Han started in Euiwang in 2014.

419
00:26:23,700 --> 00:26:27,000
Mr. Choi started in Gwangju. So, it was 2018.

420
00:26:27,050 --> 00:26:29,020
- Yes!
- Okay!

421
00:26:30,420 --> 00:26:32,720
Let's drink!

422
00:26:32,720 --> 00:26:35,190
Let's drink! Let's drink!

423
00:26:38,100 --> 00:26:40,800
Free drinks taste the best.

424
00:26:42,220 --> 00:26:44,160
It's been too long.

425
00:26:44,200 --> 00:26:47,500
I had no one to come with since
you were gone. I'm so happy right now.

426
00:26:47,500 --> 00:26:51,800
It's because you're too picky with people.

427
00:26:51,850 --> 00:26:54,050
Who's she? Was it Min Jeong in your department?

428
00:26:54,100 --> 00:26:56,650
- You said she's all right.
- Gosh.

429
00:26:56,650 --> 00:26:59,420
I can't hang out with the MZ Generation.

430
00:26:59,420 --> 00:27:02,500
Kids these days don't have
respect for their elders.

431
00:27:03,400 --> 00:27:07,500
You can't be that elder,
who's only two years older, right?

432
00:27:10,100 --> 00:27:13,380
Between her and I,

433
00:27:13,400 --> 00:27:16,800
- there's a hurdle, which is her eyelashes.
- What?

434
00:27:16,820 --> 00:27:19,880
She wears eyelashes that look like fingers.

435
00:27:19,880 --> 00:27:21,860
Whenever she blinks when I'm talking to her,

436
00:27:21,860 --> 00:27:24,600
I feel the wind on my face from her eyelashes.

437
00:27:24,600 --> 00:27:28,150
- I can't hear anything she says.
- That makes no sense.

438
00:27:28,150 --> 00:27:30,490
It's true.

439
00:27:35,640 --> 00:27:37,350
What's this?

440
00:27:40,230 --> 00:27:41,790
What is it?

441
00:27:41,790 --> 00:27:43,440
What?

442
00:27:45,500 --> 00:27:48,600
Lee Hyo Ri, what is it?

443
00:28:23,430 --> 00:28:25,000
Sorry.

444
00:28:27,270 --> 00:28:29,460
Fine. I'm not sorry.

445
00:28:34,550 --> 00:28:37,400
I won't tell you to cheer up.

446
00:28:43,460 --> 00:28:45,710
Let's have fun.

447
00:28:47,460 --> 00:28:50,330
Quit your silly studies

448
00:28:50,330 --> 00:28:52,450
and do whatever you want.

449
00:28:52,450 --> 00:28:53,860
Fail, ruin things,

450
00:28:53,860 --> 00:28:56,680
and live a messy and fun life.

451
00:28:56,680 --> 00:28:58,130
Okay?

452
00:28:58,130 --> 00:29:00,060
Let's really live however we want.

453
00:29:00,060 --> 00:29:01,500
I swear I will.

454
00:29:01,500 --> 00:29:04,130
Yes. That's it. Okay.

455
00:29:05,200 --> 00:29:07,860
I'll go to Cheonghae when the semester ends.

456
00:29:07,900 --> 00:29:10,100
Let's have tons of fun.

457
00:29:10,100 --> 00:29:13,360
We sure will. You have to come, okay?

458
00:29:13,360 --> 00:29:15,470
Okay, I'll come.

459
00:29:28,800 --> 00:29:30,310
I'm off.

460
00:30:00,130 --> 00:30:02,240
<i>Cheers!</i>

461
00:30:09,630 --> 00:30:10,960
Someone's here.

462
00:30:10,960 --> 00:30:12,360
- What?
- Hyo Ri.

463
00:30:12,360 --> 00:30:14,560
- Lee Hyo Ri!
- Lee Hyo Ri!

464
00:30:21,780 --> 00:30:23,970
Manager Lee, she's so pretty.

465
00:30:23,970 --> 00:30:27,230
Right? She's my daughter.

466
00:30:27,230 --> 00:30:30,080
She's pretty because she's my daughter.

467
00:30:48,960 --> 00:30:51,860
[Hyo Ri]

468
00:30:51,860 --> 00:30:53,860
[Are you dead? Come quickly]

469
00:31:02,160 --> 00:31:03,800
<i>Daughter, where are you?</i>

470
00:31:03,800 --> 00:31:06,300
- Dad.
<i>- You scared me.</i>

471
00:31:06,300 --> 00:31:08,880
<i>Hey, why aren't you home yet?</i>

472
00:31:08,880 --> 00:31:10,540
<i>Where are you?</i>

473
00:31:10,540 --> 00:31:12,850
<i>Should I come arrest you?</i>

474
00:31:12,850 --> 00:31:14,480
Dad.

475
00:31:14,480 --> 00:31:15,840
<i>What?</i>

476
00:31:15,840 --> 00:31:18,190
<i>I have no money.</i>

477
00:31:18,190 --> 00:31:20,210
<i>Mom caught me giving you money and...</i>

478
00:31:20,210 --> 00:31:23,330
<i>Hey, I'll die if I get caught again.</i>

479
00:31:25,820 --> 00:31:27,420
<i>What?</i>

480
00:31:27,420 --> 00:31:29,400
<i>What's wrong, Sook?</i>

481
00:31:29,400 --> 00:31:31,300
<i>What's wrong?</i>

482
00:31:31,330 --> 00:31:32,950
Dad,

483
00:31:33,770 --> 00:31:36,500
H-Hyo Ri...

484
00:31:39,170 --> 00:31:41,830
She's sick.

485
00:31:41,900 --> 00:31:45,380
But not knowing that,

486
00:31:45,380 --> 00:31:48,780
I texted asking if she was dead...

487
00:31:52,230 --> 00:31:54,820
What do I do, Dad?

488
00:31:55,910 --> 00:31:58,810
What do I do, Dad?

489
00:31:59,710 --> 00:32:03,290
Dad, what do I do?

490
00:32:04,600 --> 00:32:07,480
<i>Oh, no... Gosh.</i>

491
00:32:07,480 --> 00:32:09,090
<i>Sook.</i>

492
00:32:12,110 --> 00:32:14,170
Drink, drink.

493
00:32:15,260 --> 00:32:17,310
Have another glass. Have another glass.

494
00:32:17,310 --> 00:32:19,480
- Have some.
- Okay.

495
00:32:22,260 --> 00:32:24,330
Don't be like that.

496
00:32:24,330 --> 00:32:26,470
Thank you.

497
00:32:27,870 --> 00:32:29,950
That doesn't taste good.

498
00:32:29,950 --> 00:32:31,970
I don't get it.

499
00:32:36,700 --> 00:32:40,700
Just like Anchorwoman Baek Ji Yeon,

500
00:32:40,700 --> 00:32:42,720
I'll become a carrier woman.

501
00:32:42,720 --> 00:32:44,480
You want to become a carrier?

502
00:32:44,480 --> 00:32:46,880
Career. Not carrier, you fool.

503
00:32:46,880 --> 00:32:49,020
Don't be such a stickler.

504
00:32:49,020 --> 00:32:50,820
You understand what I was saying.

505
00:32:50,820 --> 00:32:53,510
Why would you be nitpicky?

506
00:32:53,510 --> 00:32:55,870
If you're so smart,

507
00:32:55,870 --> 00:32:58,300
why do you get chicken and kitchen mixed up?

508
00:32:58,300 --> 00:33:00,310
That's not...

509
00:33:03,180 --> 00:33:04,890
I'll be back.

510
00:33:12,430 --> 00:33:14,780
- I'll pour you one.
- By the way...

511
00:33:14,780 --> 00:33:17,060
Hyo Ri, you know...

512
00:33:17,900 --> 00:33:20,870
Looking at her face,

513
00:33:22,630 --> 00:33:25,130
I can tell she had an...

514
00:33:25,130 --> 00:33:29,670
appendix surgery when she was in the 9th grade.

515
00:33:29,670 --> 00:33:32,450
How did you know that?

516
00:33:34,150 --> 00:33:36,300
To be honest,

517
00:33:36,300 --> 00:33:40,030
that's why I became good friends with your mom.

518
00:33:42,190 --> 00:33:44,100
The end has to be thicker.

519
00:33:44,100 --> 00:33:45,830
Apply more on the side.

520
00:33:45,830 --> 00:33:48,310
Why don't you do it yourself?

521
00:33:48,310 --> 00:33:50,530
Why is she nitpicking?

522
00:33:50,530 --> 00:33:52,090
I'm not nitpicking.

523
00:33:52,090 --> 00:33:54,970
It's a necessary step. Fix it.

524
00:33:56,580 --> 00:33:59,300
<i>A female manager at a construction site?</i>

525
00:33:59,300 --> 00:34:01,840
<i>Gosh, it's hard.</i>

526
00:34:01,900 --> 00:34:06,980
<i>You can't do that unless you're really gutsy.</i>

527
00:34:06,980 --> 00:34:09,380
All the people in this field...

528
00:34:09,380 --> 00:34:12,530
have quite a bit of temper.

529
00:34:14,500 --> 00:34:16,990
Director, remove the pins

530
00:34:16,990 --> 00:34:19,100
and polish the surface, too.

531
00:34:21,260 --> 00:34:24,700
I was going to do all that, anyway.

532
00:34:24,700 --> 00:34:26,900
I was going to check this first.

533
00:34:26,900 --> 00:34:29,260
I already had a plan, okay?

