00:34:29,260 --> 00:34:31,550
Do I have to read your mind, too?

535
00:34:31,550 --> 00:34:33,670
Work in the normal order.

536
00:34:33,670 --> 00:34:35,680
Do you know how to finish walls?

537
00:34:35,680 --> 00:34:38,140
I'm working hard. If you know nothing...

538
00:34:38,200 --> 00:34:41,560
She was obviously right,

539
00:34:41,560 --> 00:34:45,460
but she kept giving orders.

540
00:34:45,500 --> 00:34:49,600
To be honest, I didn't like her at first, either.

541
00:34:49,600 --> 00:34:51,830
A lot of you were...

542
00:34:51,830 --> 00:34:55,200
determined to teach her a lesson, right?

543
00:34:55,200 --> 00:34:57,800
Remember Mr. Park from Taean Supplies?

544
00:34:57,800 --> 00:35:00,680
- Yes, yes.
- He even slapped her in the face.

545
00:35:00,680 --> 00:35:03,860
Because the order got canceled.

546
00:35:03,900 --> 00:35:07,140
But she didn't even bat an eye.

547
00:35:07,140 --> 00:35:09,500
Gosh, she's tough. Yes.

548
00:35:09,500 --> 00:35:13,230
I thought, "I shouldn't get involved
with her," at first.

549
00:35:13,230 --> 00:35:14,960
But...

550
00:35:18,530 --> 00:35:20,680
Geez.

551
00:35:32,000 --> 00:35:34,700
Yes, it's me. Did you have lunch?

552
00:35:35,570 --> 00:35:37,990
Hey, you need to take care of yourself.

553
00:35:38,000 --> 00:35:42,600
Tell the nurse you slept through
the lunch hour and eat right now.

554
00:35:42,600 --> 00:35:45,200
You need to care for yourself if I can't be there.

555
00:35:45,200 --> 00:35:47,380
Tell them right now.

556
00:35:59,390 --> 00:36:00,970
<i>She was crying.</i>

557
00:36:01,800 --> 00:36:04,690
<i>She said her daughter was hospitalized.</i>

558
00:36:05,600 --> 00:36:09,200
But we were having a work emergency, too.

559
00:36:09,210 --> 00:36:12,220
Imagine how she must've felt.

560
00:36:14,420 --> 00:36:17,930
<i>I saw her forcing herself to eat</i>

561
00:36:18,000 --> 00:36:21,700
<i>while crying silently.</i>

562
00:36:24,010 --> 00:36:26,530
<i>Gosh, seeing that,</i>

563
00:36:27,600 --> 00:36:30,220
<i>I finally thought,</i>

564
00:36:33,970 --> 00:36:35,420
<i>"She's...</i>

565
00:36:37,480 --> 00:36:39,700
<i>trying to survive, too."</i>

566
00:36:41,630 --> 00:36:43,100
That was...

567
00:36:43,100 --> 00:36:46,210
the moment I fell for her.

568
00:36:46,210 --> 00:36:47,480
That's right.

569
00:36:47,480 --> 00:36:50,410
- I'm sure everyone here is the same.
- Of course.

570
00:36:50,410 --> 00:36:51,500
Yes.

571
00:36:51,500 --> 00:36:56,700
Manager Lee's frustrating yet simple spirit.

572
00:36:56,760 --> 00:36:58,640
You're hopeless once you fall for that.

573
00:36:58,640 --> 00:37:02,630
I'm hopeless. I'm hopeless. Help me.

574
00:37:09,800 --> 00:37:13,730
I got everyone a hangover cure.

575
00:37:20,700 --> 00:37:23,000
Manager Lee is the best!

576
00:37:37,850 --> 00:37:39,900
I haven't drunk this much in a while.

577
00:37:39,900 --> 00:37:41,600
I feel... I feel sick.

578
00:37:41,600 --> 00:37:44,080
Hey, if you throw up in here,

579
00:37:44,080 --> 00:37:47,200
forget the house. Our friendship is over.

580
00:37:47,200 --> 00:37:51,900
Should you hang a bag on your ears?

581
00:37:53,900 --> 00:37:55,800
Wait a minute.

582
00:37:55,800 --> 00:37:58,720
Gosh. Gosh. What do I do?

583
00:37:58,720 --> 00:38:01,400
Gosh, I don't know.

584
00:38:01,400 --> 00:38:04,300
- I don't know, don't know, don't know.
- What's with her?

585
00:38:04,300 --> 00:38:07,520
W-What's the problem?

586
00:38:08,910 --> 00:38:10,100
Oppa,

587
00:38:11,000 --> 00:38:14,500
it turns out you're the...

588
00:38:14,500 --> 00:38:17,210
first man to visit our place.

589
00:38:17,210 --> 00:38:19,760
Gosh! What do I do?

590
00:38:21,450 --> 00:38:24,150
I don't know what to do! Gosh.

591
00:38:24,150 --> 00:38:27,140
<i>I feel so shy.</i>

592
00:38:31,960 --> 00:38:33,130
Hey.

593
00:38:33,130 --> 00:38:35,960
I'm totally fine. What are you doing?

594
00:38:35,960 --> 00:38:37,680
Let go.

595
00:38:38,430 --> 00:38:39,250
I'm okay.

596
00:38:39,250 --> 00:38:41,030
You bought everyone a hangover cure.

597
00:38:41,030 --> 00:38:43,500
Why didn't you get one for yourself?

598
00:38:43,500 --> 00:38:44,820
That's what I'm saying.

599
00:38:44,820 --> 00:38:46,790
Ahjussi, I'll stop by the convenience store.

600
00:38:46,790 --> 00:38:49,490
Okay, okay. See you.

601
00:38:49,490 --> 00:38:51,390
Here, sit.

602
00:38:52,670 --> 00:38:54,380
Geez.

603
00:39:01,180 --> 00:39:02,660
Okay...

604
00:39:14,900 --> 00:39:16,800
Where's the light switch?

605
00:39:16,800 --> 00:39:19,180
Right there. Behind the door.

606
00:39:19,180 --> 00:39:20,300
The light.

607
00:39:21,980 --> 00:39:23,110
Here.

608
00:39:23,110 --> 00:39:25,360
Drink water and sober up.

609
00:39:25,360 --> 00:39:27,360
Come to your senses.

610
00:39:31,360 --> 00:39:34,200
Stop smiling. I don't want to get attached.

611
00:39:35,160 --> 00:39:37,260
No! No.

612
00:39:37,300 --> 00:39:40,400
No, don't get attached to me. No, no.

613
00:39:41,950 --> 00:39:43,650
That'd be hopeless.

614
00:39:43,700 --> 00:39:46,840
Because I don't want people to see my true charm,

615
00:39:46,840 --> 00:39:50,400
I've been hiding it so hard.

616
00:39:50,400 --> 00:39:53,500
So, don't get attached.

617
00:39:53,500 --> 00:39:55,400
Okay? I made it clear.

618
00:39:55,400 --> 00:39:58,300
I can't be responsible, okay?

619
00:40:08,600 --> 00:40:12,100
Oppa, you know what?

620
00:40:13,500 --> 00:40:15,830
Your eyes...

621
00:40:16,750 --> 00:40:18,940
haven't aged at all?

622
00:40:21,740 --> 00:40:24,200
You're still handsome.

623
00:40:25,620 --> 00:40:28,940
That makes me so happy.

624
00:40:39,000 --> 00:40:42,900
Okay. Drink water and sober up first.

625
00:40:51,970 --> 00:40:54,670
You don't know how it feels, do you?

626
00:40:55,910 --> 00:40:57,510
How it feels...

627
00:40:58,560 --> 00:41:02,100
when you're unsure if you're

628
00:41:02,100 --> 00:41:07,410
facing the truth or avoiding it.
That weird feeling.

629
00:41:08,320 --> 00:41:10,980
You're not okay at all,

630
00:41:12,000 --> 00:41:14,370
but you're also okay.

631
00:41:22,150 --> 00:41:24,350
I know it too well.

632
00:42:01,050 --> 00:42:03,000
Bo Hyeon,

633
00:42:03,000 --> 00:42:06,930
Mom has to catch a flight now. Okay?

634
00:42:29,640 --> 00:42:32,030
<i>The feeling when you deceive yourself.</i>

635
00:42:33,100 --> 00:42:35,430
<i>Because you have to hang in there,</i>

636
00:42:36,710 --> 00:42:39,950
you try to appear okay.

637
00:43:02,600 --> 00:43:04,750
- Mom is sleeping.
- Sorry.

638
00:43:04,750 --> 00:43:06,570
It's okay.

639
00:43:06,570 --> 00:43:07,850
Mom.

640
00:43:07,850 --> 00:43:09,570
Wake up, Ms. Lee.

641
00:43:09,600 --> 00:43:12,070
- Get up. Sleep inside.
- Yes, yes.

642
00:43:12,070 --> 00:43:13,600
Yes.

643
00:43:13,600 --> 00:43:16,450
- Yes, that's a good girl.
- Your arm.

644
00:43:16,450 --> 00:43:18,020
Go to bed.

645
00:44:25,910 --> 00:44:28,080
Should I make you some tea?

646
00:44:38,820 --> 00:44:40,850
Here you go.

647
00:44:42,910 --> 00:44:44,690
Is Mom sleeping?

648
00:44:44,690 --> 00:44:45,850
Yes.

649
00:44:45,850 --> 00:44:49,090
Her only strength is falling asleep immediately.

650
00:44:49,090 --> 00:44:50,600
I know.

651
00:44:50,600 --> 00:44:53,200
She should be on a talent show.

652
00:45:06,900 --> 00:45:08,390
Not bad, right?

653
00:45:08,390 --> 00:45:10,010
It's nice.

654
00:45:15,810 --> 00:45:17,330
By the way,

655
00:45:18,430 --> 00:45:21,170
why are you against building the house?

656
00:45:24,470 --> 00:45:27,920
My mom's life keeps changing because of me.

657
00:45:27,920 --> 00:45:29,940
I find it burdensome.

658
00:45:32,030 --> 00:45:34,410
My mom...

659
00:45:34,410 --> 00:45:36,440
never got to live her life.

660
00:45:36,500 --> 00:45:39,290
She always put me first.

661
00:45:39,290 --> 00:45:42,200
But she's making a decision like this again.

662
00:45:42,200 --> 00:45:45,500
It makes me angry, and it upsets me.

663
00:45:47,640 --> 00:45:49,720
At first,

664
00:45:49,720 --> 00:45:53,370
when she told me she'll build a house,

665
00:45:53,370 --> 00:45:55,590
I asked her...

666
00:45:56,460 --> 00:45:58,280
why she wants to.

667
00:46:00,900 --> 00:46:02,800
She said she's trying to live.

668
00:46:03,790 --> 00:46:06,720
To live a fun life with you.

669
00:46:08,920 --> 00:46:11,370
Her reason for building a house must be

670
00:46:11,370 --> 00:46:15,140
the same as why you first came to Cheonghae.

671
00:46:15,200 --> 00:46:20,500
It's the desire to do what you want
to do without further delay.

672
00:46:36,200 --> 00:46:37,820
Go inside.

673
00:46:46,600 --> 00:46:49,200
- Get some rest.
- Thank you.

674
00:47:25,140 --> 00:47:28,090
<i>You need to care for yourself if I can't be there.</i>

675
00:47:28,090 --> 00:47:29,940
<i>Tell them right now.</i>

676
00:47:39,100 --> 00:47:40,470
Ex...

677
00:47:40,470 --> 00:47:42,300
Excuse...

678
00:49:54,470 --> 00:49:57,520
I took my time because
I thought you were sleeping.

679
00:49:58,520 --> 00:50:01,230
Your acting skills haven't improved.

680
00:50:02,100 --> 00:50:05,830
Hey, by chance, last night...

681
00:50:05,830 --> 00:50:08,570
Of course, you threw a drunken tantrum.

682
00:50:08,570 --> 00:50:11,630
Mr. Ryu seemed very shocked.

683
00:50:12,790 --> 00:50:15,730
I can't reveal my true self to him yet.

684
00:50:16,700 --> 00:50:20,300
I couldn't control myself because
I hadn't drunk in a while.

685
00:50:22,180 --> 00:50:23,950
Is this my room?

686
00:50:23,950 --> 00:50:25,560
Looks like yours, telling from its size.

687
00:50:25,560 --> 00:50:27,930
Why are they so close? Put them further apart.

688
00:50:29,440 --> 00:50:32,050
Why are you suddenly making a suggestion?

689
00:50:32,050 --> 00:50:33,970
Let's build the house.

690
00:50:34,000 --> 00:50:36,990
And do it right if you're going to.

691
00:50:38,000 --> 00:50:40,100
Are you serious?

692
00:50:40,110 --> 00:50:41,100
Are you on board?

693
00:50:41,100 --> 00:50:43,700
Yes, I'm on board.

694
00:50:43,700 --> 00:50:46,070
Do you need my thumbprint or something?

695
00:50:49,520 --> 00:50:52,010
Eat quickly. Mr. Ryu will be here soon.

696
00:51:07,240 --> 00:51:09,730
Wow, you're an amazing driver.

697
00:51:09,800 --> 00:51:13,710
It feels like I'm riding
a five-star hotel mattress.

698
00:51:13,710 --> 00:51:16,820
What's the point? My customer is
either asleep or drunk.

699
00:51:16,820 --> 00:51:20,060
She's unable to notice my driving skills.

700
00:51:22,380 --> 00:51:24,580
Ahjussi,

701
00:51:24,600 --> 00:51:27,100
can we have a full-sized window
in the living room?

702
00:51:27,100 --> 00:51:28,440
- Full-sized window?
- Yes.

703
00:51:28,440 --> 00:51:29,700
Full-sized window.

704
00:51:29,700 --> 00:51:32,080
Yes, that'd look nice.

705
00:51:32,100 --> 00:51:35,560
But that'd raise the heating cost, no ventilation,

706
00:51:35,560 --> 00:51:38,450
and it provides no privacy.

707
00:51:39,900 --> 00:51:46,400
Can we have a screening or
listening room in the basement?

708
00:51:46,460 --> 00:51:48,100
That sounds good.

709
00:51:48,100 --> 00:51:52,300
But the basement gets no fresh air,
and it gets moist.

710
00:51:52,300 --> 00:51:54,950
We'd have to give up on a portion
of the yard space

711
00:51:55,000 --> 00:51:58,970
and it'd cost a lot. It'd be better to add a story.

712
00:51:58,970 --> 00:52:01,730
If you'd do everything the way you like,

713
00:52:01,730 --> 00:52:03,750
don't call it "Hyo Ri's house."

714
00:52:03,750 --> 00:52:05,550
Call it "Ji An's house" instead.

715
00:52:05,550 --> 00:52:08,380
No, call it "Tyrant Lee Ji An's
However-I-want House."

716
00:52:08,380 --> 00:52:10,900
"I'm-the-King. Suppress-your-opinion House."

717
00:52:10,900 --> 00:52:12,230
How does that sound?

718
00:52:12,230 --> 00:52:14,400
I'm being nice, yet you're talking back?

719
00:52:14,400 --> 00:52:16,980
- Talking back? I'm kowtowing cautiously.
- Kow-

720
00:52:16,980 --> 00:52:19,870
Do you know what "kowtow" means?

721
00:52:19,870 --> 00:52:22,200
Do you know what "nice" means?

722
00:52:22,200 --> 00:52:24,500
Gosh, she has to have the last word.

723
00:52:24,500 --> 00:52:26,580
You know I do.

724
00:52:56,000 --> 00:52:58,360
The bottom and the pillars weren't aligned.

725
00:52:58,360 --> 00:53:00,550
We secured it with a belt.

726
00:53:00,550 --> 00:53:01,850
Okay.

727
00:53:01,850 --> 00:53:03,280
- Cheol Min.
- What?

728
00:53:03,280 --> 00:53:04,930
- You're doing great.
- Really?

729
00:53:04,930 --> 00:53:07,840
- Can I be a chief, too?
- The drain pipe will come out here.

730
00:53:07,840 --> 00:53:10,280
You'll keep the circuit breaker where it is, right?

731
00:53:10,280 --> 00:53:12,160
Yes. Focus on waterproofing the kitchen.

732
00:53:12,160 --> 00:53:14,160
Okay. I'll have a look.

733
00:53:15,530 --> 00:53:17,940
How big of a flat tie do you need?

734
00:53:18,930 --> 00:53:21,140
We'll have the 350 ones.

735
00:53:21,140 --> 00:53:22,980
Won't you measure with a ruler?

736
00:53:22,980 --> 00:53:25,060
Follow the basic rules.

737
00:53:25,060 --> 00:53:27,620
I know it's annoying, but measuring with a ruler

738
00:53:27,620 --> 00:53:29,810
is important in this job.

739
00:53:29,810 --> 00:53:32,010
How will you train your juniors later?

740
00:53:32,010 --> 00:53:33,580
Okay.

741
00:53:35,400 --> 00:53:37,570
- 400.
- So?

742
00:53:37,570 --> 00:53:40,190
Since we're adding the wedge pins,

743
00:53:40,190 --> 00:53:42,500
we'll get the 400 ones.

744
00:53:42,500 --> 00:53:45,960
I said work is about the attitude, not experience.

745
00:53:45,960 --> 00:53:48,290
If you're sloppy with the basics,

746
00:53:48,290 --> 00:53:52,410
you end up looking sloppy
without showing off your strength.

747
00:53:52,410 --> 00:53:54,210
Take a 30-minute break.

748
00:53:54,210 --> 00:53:56,500
- The sun is too strong.
- Okay.

749
00:54:00,620 --> 00:54:03,700
Wow, I was a bit surprised just now.

750
00:54:03,700 --> 00:54:05,550
You looked like a good senior just now.

751
00:54:05,550 --> 00:54:07,430
Are you picking a fight on this hot day?

752
00:54:07,430 --> 00:54:08,750
What are you talking about?

753
00:54:08,750 --> 00:54:10,780
A compliment is supposed to make a whale dance.

754
00:54:10,780 --> 00:54:13,750
Cool senior, Manager Lee, fighting.

755
00:54:34,980 --> 00:54:36,100
Let's eat!

756
00:54:36,100 --> 00:54:37,900
Welcome!

757
00:54:37,900 --> 00:54:40,100
I'll eat first! Hello.

758
00:54:40,100 --> 00:54:41,070
Hello.

759
00:54:41,070 --> 00:54:44,490
Wow, I haven't tasted your cooking in a while.

760
00:54:44,490 --> 00:54:46,780
This is what a proper spread looks like.

761
00:54:46,780 --> 00:54:49,200
Yes. I put extra effort into it.

762
00:54:49,200 --> 00:54:52,200
Please work extra hard after eating it.

763
00:54:52,250 --> 00:54:54,330
- Thank you for the meal!
- Applause!

764
00:54:54,330 --> 00:54:56,410
Applause. Applause.

765
00:54:57,510 --> 00:54:59,580
Help yourselves.

766
00:55:03,310 --> 00:55:04,910
Seventy.

767
00:55:10,460 --> 00:55:11,920
Aren't you eating?

768
00:55:11,920 --> 00:55:14,650
I'm not hungry right now.

769
00:55:14,650 --> 00:55:16,900
Why is the plastering surface so rough?

770
00:55:17,900 --> 00:55:19,080
Eat without me.

771
00:55:19,080 --> 00:55:21,850
I'll eat when I'm hungry later.

772
00:55:55,020 --> 00:55:56,900
We'll leave now.

773
00:55:56,900 --> 00:55:58,900
You did so much. Thank you.

774
00:55:58,900 --> 00:56:00,890
We managed to pull it off.

775
00:56:00,900 --> 00:56:03,810
We'll come running anytime if you call us.

776
00:56:03,810 --> 00:56:05,660
I know. Thank you so much.

777
00:56:05,700 --> 00:56:08,200
- It's okay. That's enough.
- Treat us to a meal later.

778
00:56:08,260 --> 00:56:09,970
- We'll hang out again.
- I'm going to Seoul next month.

779
00:56:09,970 --> 00:56:10,990
Really? Really?

780
00:56:10,990 --> 00:56:12,340
We'll be seeing you.

781
00:56:12,340 --> 00:56:13,680
- We'll go.
- Bye. Thank you.

782
00:56:13,680 --> 00:56:14,780
Live well.

783
00:56:14,780 --> 00:56:17,140
- Thank you.
- Fighting.

784
00:56:35,190 --> 00:56:37,550
Okay. Let's work. Let's work.

785
00:56:37,550 --> 00:56:39,760
It's moving day.

786
00:56:39,760 --> 00:56:41,770
Be careful.

787
00:56:44,570 --> 00:56:45,940
Give it to me.

788
00:56:45,940 --> 00:56:47,940
It's so heavy.

789
00:56:47,940 --> 00:56:49,660
Let me help you.

790
00:56:49,660 --> 00:56:51,200
No, I'm okay.

791
00:56:51,200 --> 00:56:52,280
To Hyo Ri's room, right?

792
00:56:52,280 --> 00:56:54,500
- Yes. Hyo Ri.
- This way.

793
00:56:54,500 --> 00:56:55,700
- Do you need help?
- No. It's okay.

794
00:56:55,700 --> 00:56:57,860
Don't go with him...

795
00:56:57,860 --> 00:56:58,860
Hey...

796
00:56:58,860 --> 00:57:01,210
Don't go with him, I said.

797
00:57:02,020 --> 00:57:03,950
Gosh. Looks heavy. Be careful.

798
00:57:03,950 --> 00:57:06,670
- Use your muscles.
- Be careful. Be careful.

799
00:57:06,670 --> 00:57:09,380
Gosh, not this way. Go back.

800
00:57:09,380 --> 00:57:12,040
That's my meal ticket. Not this way.

